56
00:03:17,200 --> 00:03:19,300
What are you talking about?

57
00:03:19,300 --> 00:03:21,520
Why is he my baby?

58
00:03:21,520 --> 00:03:23,130
I don't have much time so listen.

59
00:03:23,130 --> 00:03:25,850
I was going to raise him regardless of you.

60
00:03:25,850 --> 00:03:29,320
My parents agreed to help me raise him while I study abroad,

61
00:03:29,320 --> 00:03:34,420
but I found out my mom was trying to send him somewhere without me knowing.

62
00:03:34,420 --> 00:03:35,780
I can never let that happen.

63
00:03:35,780 --> 00:03:37,700
W-Wait, wait.

64
00:03:37,700 --> 00:03:39,830
Are you telling me to believe this?

65
00:03:39,830 --> 00:03:42,840
- What if you don't? 
 - No, I mean...

66
00:03:42,840 --> 00:03:45,760
If you suddenly tell me I'm his dad…

67
00:03:46,820 --> 00:03:50,700
Could it be the day I had the chills?

68
00:03:50,700 --> 00:03:52,730
It was just that one time.

69
00:03:52,730 --> 00:03:55,710
I told you we shouldn't have done that!

70
00:03:55,710 --> 00:03:56,750
Whatever the case…

71
00:03:56,750 --> 00:03:59,060
I'm leaving the country today.

72
00:03:59,060 --> 00:04:01,270
Please just raise him for three years.

73
00:04:01,270 --> 00:04:02,090
What?

74
00:04:02,090 --> 00:04:04,250
I'll collect him when I return from studying abroad.

75
00:04:04,250 --> 00:04:06,340
You're also responsible for this

76
00:04:06,340 --> 00:04:09,900
so just take responsibility for three years.

77
00:04:09,900 --> 00:04:12,270
I'll take care of everything afterward.

78
00:04:14,090 --> 00:04:16,320
Why do you tell me this now?

79
00:04:16,880 --> 00:04:18,070
Why so suddenly?

80
00:04:18,070 --> 00:04:20,240
I've been trying to tell you.

81
00:04:20,240 --> 00:04:22,580
Do you think it was easy for me?

82
00:04:22,580 --> 00:04:25,280
I couldn’t tell you on the phone so I wanted to see you,

83
00:04:25,280 --> 00:04:28,070
but you were always with your girlfriend.

84
00:04:28,070 --> 00:04:30,920
Why are you two never apart?

85
00:04:33,250 --> 00:04:34,900
Hey, I have to go now.

86
00:04:34,900 --> 00:04:36,650
W-Wait, no...

87
00:04:36,650 --> 00:04:38,790
H-Hold on. Hold on!

88
00:04:38,790 --> 00:04:40,990
What do I do if you give me a baby like this?

89
00:04:40,990 --> 00:04:43,600
I'm suddenly a dad? How can you do this to me?

90
00:04:43,600 --> 00:04:45,230
I'm begging you, Ho Sung.

91
00:04:45,230 --> 00:04:48,110
You're his dad.

92
00:04:48,110 --> 00:04:50,740
Will you let your child be sent somewhere unknown?

93
00:04:50,740 --> 00:04:52,690
No.

94
00:04:52,690 --> 00:04:54,560
I can't let that happen.

95
00:04:55,250 --> 00:04:58,040
Even if my mom or dad phone, don't answer.

96
00:04:58,040 --> 00:04:59,880
And don't...

97
00:05:02,440 --> 00:05:04,470
Don't ever hand the baby over.

98
00:05:04,470 --> 00:05:06,240
Got it?

99
00:05:17,350 --> 00:05:18,400
Noona...

100
00:05:18,400 --> 00:05:19,430
Noona.

101
00:05:19,430 --> 00:05:21,970
Noona! Hey, Jung Da Hye! Hey!

102
00:05:26,300 --> 00:05:28,090
What do I do?

103
00:05:37,220 --> 00:05:38,640
I talked to your mom.

104
00:05:38,640 --> 00:05:41,840
She's leaving work and coming to the school now.

105
00:05:41,840 --> 00:05:43,560
Okay.

106
00:05:43,560 --> 00:05:46,950
Did you really have no idea?

107
00:05:48,980 --> 00:05:50,630
Ms. Song...

108
00:05:50,630 --> 00:05:52,870
What do I do now?

109
00:05:52,870 --> 00:05:56,480
Am I expelled from school?

110
00:05:56,480 --> 00:05:59,430
No. Why would you be expelled?

111
00:05:59,430 --> 00:06:01,250
When your mom gets here,

112
00:06:01,250 --> 00:06:05,700
let's talk together about what to do going forward.

113
00:06:06,640 --> 00:06:09,430
It's all right. Okay?

114
00:06:23,800 --> 00:06:25,380
Can you still not reach Ho Sung?

115
00:06:25,380 --> 00:06:27,100
No, I can't.

116
00:06:28,120 --> 00:06:30,130
What is going on? Seriously.

117
00:06:30,130 --> 00:06:32,280
I can't believe it.

118
00:06:32,280 --> 00:06:33,860
What happens now?

119
00:06:33,860 --> 00:06:36,640
Can he still attend school?

120
00:06:36,640 --> 00:06:38,500
I don't know.

121
00:06:39,850 --> 00:06:42,350
Do you know where Ho Sung lives? Should we visit him together?

122
00:06:42,350 --> 00:06:45,500
His parents must be freaking out right now.

123
00:06:45,500 --> 00:06:48,120
I think we should wait.

124
00:06:50,670 --> 00:06:51,710
Here...

125
00:06:51,710 --> 00:06:54,850
We should eat first and calm our startled hearts.

126
00:06:57,670 --> 00:06:59,080
Thank you.

127
00:07:00,260 --> 00:07:01,850
Oh, right.

128
00:07:01,850 --> 00:07:04,130
Why did Young Joo come by last night?

129
00:07:04,130 --> 00:07:05,720
By chance...

130
00:07:05,720 --> 00:07:08,300
It's not because of me, right?

131
00:07:13,190 --> 00:07:15,140
It's not.

132
00:07:16,850 --> 00:07:19,060
We had something to work out.

133
00:07:19,060 --> 00:07:21,160
Are there more things left to work out?

134
00:07:21,160 --> 00:07:23,650
When will everything be worked out?

135
00:07:24,240 --> 00:07:26,770
Just how much is tangled up?

136
00:07:27,880 --> 00:07:31,850
I think it all worked out now.

137
00:07:32,930 --> 00:07:35,550
You guys really took your time.

138
00:07:36,690 --> 00:07:39,800
Still, I'm glad.

139
00:07:55,980 --> 00:07:57,590
Calm down.

140
00:07:57,590 --> 00:07:59,880
How long will you keep crying?

141
00:08:00,630 --> 00:08:02,790
What a jerk!

142
00:08:05,540 --> 00:08:07,710
Is it something to cry over this much?

143
00:08:07,710 --> 00:08:09,050
You weren't even dating him.

144
00:08:09,050 --> 00:08:11,420
I was going to!

145
00:08:11,420 --> 00:08:13,520
Starting today.

146
00:08:15,360 --> 00:08:17,630
Good thing you didn't.

147
00:08:17,630 --> 00:08:20,380
But is that really Ji Ho Sung's child?

148
00:08:20,380 --> 00:08:21,910
I don't know.

149
00:08:21,910 --> 00:08:25,820
I heard his ex-girlfriend stopped seeing him,

150
00:08:25,820 --> 00:08:27,000
but what is this?

151
00:08:27,000 --> 00:08:29,910
I'm ruined.

152
00:08:31,730 --> 00:08:33,010
What do you mean, "ruined"?

153
00:08:33,010 --> 00:08:35,920
Just get the people around you and your emotions in order.

154
00:08:35,920 --> 00:08:37,340
Of course, I will.

155
00:08:37,340 --> 00:08:40,080
I tell that b*stard to enjoy raising his ex-girlfriend's baby.

156
00:08:40,080 --> 00:08:42,240
I'll be fine without him.

157
00:08:43,230 --> 00:08:46,440
- That's a little much. 
 - What?

158
00:08:46,440 --> 00:08:49,400
I'm really good at cutting things off.

159
00:08:49,400 --> 00:08:52,060
I'm not like you.

160
00:08:52,060 --> 00:08:53,450
Whatever.

161
00:08:53,450 --> 00:08:56,460
You can't forget Young Joo even after he dumped you.

162
00:08:56,460 --> 00:09:01,120
- Hey. When did I say I can't— 
 - I'd never do that.

163
00:09:01,120 --> 00:09:03,590
I'm completely fine.

164
00:09:03,590 --> 00:09:06,100
Hey, why would I cry?

165
00:09:06,100 --> 00:09:07,960
That's funny.

166
00:09:09,220 --> 00:09:11,080
I'm going now.

167
00:09:13,800 --> 00:09:15,970
Hey. Go Eun Bi!

168
00:09:53,500 --> 00:09:55,030
Grandpa!

169
00:09:57,140 --> 00:09:58,150
What?

170
00:09:58,150 --> 00:10:01,370
Why did you come out here at night?

171
00:10:01,370 --> 00:10:02,840
Are you okay?

172
00:10:02,840 --> 00:10:04,380
- Does it hurt? 
 - No.

173
00:10:04,380 --> 00:10:05,380
Not at all.

174
00:10:05,380 --> 00:10:07,020
I'm fine.

175
00:10:07,020 --> 00:10:08,830
Why did you come out here?

176
00:10:09,650 --> 00:10:11,910
You haven't taken your medicine again, have you?

177
00:10:12,550 --> 00:10:14,360
Why do you keep forgetting?

178
00:10:14,360 --> 00:10:17,540
I put it on the fridge door because you kept forgetting.

179
00:10:17,540 --> 00:10:21,500
Oh, I was running late, and I left in a rush.

180
00:10:21,500 --> 00:10:22,920
I'll take them later.

181
00:10:22,920 --> 00:10:24,750
- Right now. 
 - Pardon?

182
00:10:26,010 --> 00:10:28,030
Geez, all right.

183
00:10:34,160 --> 00:10:35,730
I'll take the trash.

184
00:10:36,900 --> 00:10:38,340
Water.

185
00:10:43,700 --> 00:10:46,590
I'm perfectly fine.

186
00:10:46,590 --> 00:10:49,350
You must be tired. Why did you come all the way over here?

187
00:10:49,350 --> 00:10:50,670
Hurry and go home.

188
00:10:50,670 --> 00:10:52,260
It's cold.

189
00:10:52,260 --> 00:10:53,540
Do you have to do that now?

190
00:10:53,540 --> 00:10:55,090
I'm almost done anyway.

191
00:10:55,090 --> 00:10:56,970
Go home. Go on.

192
00:10:57,920 --> 00:10:59,620
- Let's do it together. 
 - What?

193
00:10:59,620 --> 00:11:01,510
Geez.

194
00:11:02,350 --> 00:11:04,050
Let's see.

195
00:11:05,290 --> 00:11:07,360
I just have to stack them like this, right?

196
00:11:19,720 --> 00:11:21,050
Hey.

197
00:11:21,050 --> 00:11:22,560
What's up with your minion?

198
00:11:22,560 --> 00:11:25,150
A shocking plot twist. Why is his personal life so dirty?

199
00:11:25,150 --> 00:11:26,890
He looks innocent,

200
00:11:26,890 --> 00:11:29,550
